# Kotlin Standards

## Error Handling -- Result<T> Mandatory

All external operations (network, database, sensor, crypto, math) must return `Result<T>`:

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD -- throws, no error info
fun calculateGrip(rainfall: Double, temp: Double): Double = ...

// ✅ GOOD
fun calculateGrip(rainfall: Double, temp: Double): Result<GripIndex> = try {
    require(rainfall >= 0.0) { "Rainfall cannot be negative: $rainfall mm" }
    Result.success(GripIndex(score = computeScore(rainfall, temp)))
} catch (e: IllegalArgumentException) {
    Result.failure(e)
} catch (e: Exception) {
    Result.failure(Exception("Grip calculation failed: ${e.localizedMessage}"))
}
```

## Units -- Strictly Metric, Strictly 24h

```kotlin
// ❌ BANNED -- imperial, AM/PM
val speedMph = 68.0
val eta = "2:30 PM"

// ✅ REQUIRED
val speedKmh = 110.0          // km/h
val tempCelsius = 32.5        // °C
val rainfallMm = 2.4          // mm
val distanceKm = 14.7         // km
val eta24h = "14:30"          // HH:mm strict 24h
val arrivalTime = "08:45:00"  // HH:mm:ss for precision
```

Use `java.time.LocalTime` with `DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern("HH:mm")` for all time operations.

## Coroutines & Flow

```kotlin
// Suspend functions for one-shot operations
suspend fun syncWeather(): Result<Unit>

// Flow for continuous streams (GPS, convoy state)
fun observeLocation(): Flow<Location>

// Always use Dispatchers explicitly in repositories
suspend fun fetchFromNetwork() = withContext(Dispatchers.IO) { ... }

// Use StateFlow for UI-observable state
private val _state = MutableStateFlow(ConvoyState.Idle)
val state: StateFlow<ConvoyState> = _state.asStateFlow()
```

## Logging -- Timber Only

```kotlin
// ❌ BANNED in all code
Log.d("SLICK", "message")
println("debug")

// ✅ REQUIRED
Timber.d("Weather node loaded: %s", nodeId)
Timber.e(exception, "GPS batch failed")
Timber.w("Thermal threshold reached: %.1f°C", tempCelsius)
```

Never log coordinates, user IDs, or any PII. Log UUIDs only.

## KDoc on Public Functions

```kotlin
/**
 * Calculates lateral crosswind force at a route node.
 *
 * Formula: crosswindKmh = windSpeedKmh * sin(|windDirDeg - bearingDeg|)
 *
 * @param windSpeedKmh Wind speed in km/h from Open-Meteo
 * @param windDirDegrees Wind direction in degrees (0-360)
 * @param bearingDegrees Route bearing at this node (0-360)
 * @return Result containing crosswind speed in km/h, or failure with cause
 */
fun calculateCrosswind(
    windSpeedKmh: Double,
    windDirDegrees: Double,
    bearingDegrees: Double,
): Result<Double>
```

## Naming Conventions

- Files: `PascalCase.kt` for classes, `camelCase.kt` for standalone functions
- Classes/Objects: `PascalCase`
- Functions/properties: `camelCase`
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` in companion objects or top-level `object Constants`
- No magic numbers -- extract to named constants

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD
if (distance > 10.0) { ... }

// ✅ GOOD
object RouteConstants {
    const val NODE_INTERVAL_KM = 10.0
    const val MAX_DETOUR_RADIUS_KM = 15.0
    const val BLE_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS = 10_000L
}
if (distance > RouteConstants.NODE_INTERVAL_KM) { ... }
```

## File Size Limits

| Type | Max Lines |
|------|-----------|
| Activity / Service | 400 |
| Composable screen | 250 |
| ViewModel | 300 |
| Repository | 300 |
| Manager / Engine | 400 |
| Utility / Extension | 150 |
| Test file | 300 |

Extract to helpers when approaching limits.
